<div class="andf-page" id="page-1">
<div class="andf-cover">
<h1 class="andf-h andf-h1">Q4 2025 Business Performance Report</h1>
<p class="andf-cover-subtitle">Executive Summary &amp; Strategic Outlook</p>
<p class="andf-cover-authors">Finance Team, Strategy Office</p>
<p class="andf-cover-date">2026-03-02</p>
<hr class="andf-cover-divider">
</div>
<p class="andf-p">Acme Corporation delivered its strongest quarter on record in Q4 2025, with revenue of <strong>$4.2 billion</strong>, a 23% increase year-over-year. Operating income grew to <strong>$1.3B</strong> as efficiency initiatives offset headcount growth. Our SaaS Annual Recurring Revenue crossed the <strong>$1 billion milestone</strong> for the first time.</p>
<div class="andf-callout andf-callout-success"><div class="andf-callout-title">✔ Record Quarter</div><p>Q4 2025 marks our highest-ever quarterly revenue, operating income, and NPS score.</p></div>
<figure class="andf-table-wrap">
<figcaption class="andf-table-caption">Table 1: Q4 2025 KPI Dashboard</figcaption>
<table class="andf-table"><thead><tr>
<th style="text-align:left">Metric</th>
<th style="text-align:right">Q4 2025</th>
<th style="text-align:right">Q4 2024</th>
<th style="text-align:center">Change</th>
<th style="text-align:center">Target</th>
</tr></thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Revenue</td>
<td style="text-align:right">$4.20B</td>
<td style="text-align:right">$3.41B</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+23%</td>
<td style="text-align:center">$4.10B ✓</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Operating Income</td>
<td style="text-align:right">$1.30B</td>
<td style="text-align:right">$0.95B</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+37%</td>
<td style="text-align:center">$1.20B ✓</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Operating Margin</td>
<td style="text-align:right">31%</td>
<td style="text-align:right">28%</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+3pp</td>
<td style="text-align:center">30% ✓</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">SaaS ARR</td>
<td style="text-align:right">$1.02B</td>
<td style="text-align:right">$0.74B</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+38%</td>
<td style="text-align:center">$1.00B ✓</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Gross Margin</td>
<td style="text-align:right">68%</td>
<td style="text-align:right">65%</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+3pp</td>
<td style="text-align:center">67% ✓</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Net Promoter Score</td>
<td style="text-align:right">72</td>
<td style="text-align:right">65</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+7</td>
<td style="text-align:center">70 ✓</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Headcount</td>
<td style="text-align:right">8,400</td>
<td style="text-align:right">7,100</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+18%</td>
<td style="text-align:center">8,500 ✓</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Customer Churn (SaaS)</td>
<td style="text-align:right">1.8%</td>
<td style="text-align:right">2.4%</td>
<td style="text-align:center">-0.6pp</td>
<td style="text-align:center">&lt;2.0% ✓</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table></figure>
<h3 class="andf-h andf-h3">By Segment</h3>
<figure class="andf-table-wrap">
<figcaption class="andf-table-caption">Table 2: Revenue by Business Segment</figcaption>
<table class="andf-table"><thead><tr>
<th style="text-align:left">Segment</th>
<th style="text-align:right">Q4 2025 ($M)</th>
<th style="text-align:right">Q4 2024 ($M)</th>
<th style="text-align:center">Growth</th>
</tr></thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Cloud SaaS</td>
<td style="text-align:right">1,850</td>
<td style="text-align:right">1,330</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+39%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Enterprise Licences</td>
<td style="text-align:right">1,100</td>
<td style="text-align:right">980</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+12%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Professional Services</td>
<td style="text-align:right">680</td>
<td style="text-align:right">620</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+10%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">Hardware &amp; Devices</td>
<td style="text-align:right">570</td>
<td style="text-align:right">480</td>
<td style="text-align:center">+19%</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left"><strong>Total</strong></td>
<td style="text-align:right"><strong>4,200</strong></td>
<td style="text-align:right"><strong>3,410</strong></td>
<td style="text-align:center"><strong>+23%</strong></td>
</tr>
</tbody></table></figure>
<div class="andf-page-num">1</div>
</div>

<div class="andf-page" id="page-2">
<div class="andf-callout andf-callout-info"><div class="andf-callout-title">ℹ SaaS Acceleration</div><p>Cloud SaaS grew 39% — significantly above our 30% target — driven by the enterprise AI platform launch in October and strong renewal rates in the financial services vertical.</p></div>
<p class="andf-p">Total operating expenses were $2.9B (69% of revenue), down from 72% in Q4 2024. The improvement reflects automation in customer support (−$42M), real estate rationalisation (−$18M), and vendor contract renegotiations (−$27M).</p>
<figure class="andf-table-wrap">
<figcaption class="andf-table-caption">Table 3: Operating Expense Breakdown</figcaption>
<table class="andf-table"><thead><tr>
<th style="text-align:left">Category</th>
<th style="text-align:right">Q4 2025 ($M)</th>
<th style="text-align:right">% of Revenue</th>
</tr></thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td style="text-align:left">R&amp;D</td>
<td style="text-align:right">840</td>
